Let $T = \{9^k : k ~ \mbox{is an integer}, 0 \le k \le 4000\}$.Given that $9^{4000}$ has 3817 digits and that its first (leftmost) digit is 9, how many elements of $T$ have 9 as their leftmost digit?
Given that the numbers in set $T$ are of the form $9^k$, we can start by looking at the pattern of the last digit of powers of $9$. 
The last digit of $9^1$ is 9, the last digit of $9^2$ is 1, the last digit of $9^3$ is 9, and so on. 
This pattern repeats every 2 powers of 9, which means we can predict the last digit of any power of 9. 
Knowing this, we can focus on finding a pattern in the last digits of numbers in set $T$.
solution: Since $9^{4000}$ has 3816 digits more than $9^1$, $4000 - 3816 = \boxed{184}$ numbers have 9 as their leftmost digits.
